                        <p>
                            Many Americans first heard of Kuwait in the 1990s when the leader of Iraq at the time, Saddam Hussein, attempted to invade and annex Kuwait. The international community responded resoundingly: over thirty nations including the U.S. pushed back the advance of the Iraqi military and halted their plans for conquest. Once liberated, Kuwait became an important staging area for Allied forces from which they could launch attacks into Iraq. Today, Kuwait continues to be an important staging area for U.S. troops and equipment as the U.S. battles ISIS / ISIL.
                        </p>

                        <p>
